INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '71a297a6-7bf3-4575-9328-83fc5e9ecc3d',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$SvelteKit URL State — Filters and Pagination Belong in the URL, Not $state$escape$,
  $escape$SvelteKit's `load()` functions are the right home for server-derived data — not `$state` runes or writable stores. For filters and pagination, encode them in `url.searchParams` and let `load()` react automatically. SvelteKit re-runs any `load()` that reads `url.searchParams` whenever those params change, so `goto()` becomes your state setter — no manual invalidation needed.

In `+page.server.ts`, read `url.searchParams` directly and return typed data. The `data` prop in `+page.svelte` updates reactively on every navigation. When a filter changes, call `goto()` with an updated `URL` object. Pass `noScroll: true` and `keepFocus: true` to prevent jarring resets on filter interactions.

Avoid mirroring `data.results` into a `$state` variable — that creates a second source of truth and silently breaks re-runs. If you need imperative invalidation (e.g., after a mutation), call `invalidate('app:results')` paired with `depends('app:results')` in `load()`, not a local state copy.

This pattern gives you bookmarkable, shareable URLs, free browser history navigation through filter states, and zero client/server sync bugs — all without a single `$state` declaration for server data.$escape$,
  $escape$// +page.server.ts
export const load = async ({ url }) => {
  const q = url.searchParams.get('q') ?? '';
  const page = Number(url.searchParams.get('page') ?? 1);
  const results = await db.search(q, page);
  return { results, q, page };
};

// +page.svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import { goto } from '$app/navigation';
  import { page } from '$app/stores';
  let { data } = $props();

  function filter(q: string) {
    const url = new URL($page.url);
    url.searchParams.set('q', q);
    url.searchParams.set('page', '1');
    goto(url, { keepFocus: true, noScroll: true });
  }
</script>$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
